  "prompt": "How are pure honey and raw honey different?",
  "response": "Here are the key differences between pure honey and raw honey:\n\nRaw Honey:\n- Minimally processed\n- Not heated or pasteurized\n- Contains natural enzymes, pollen, and propolis\n- May have small particles or crystals\n- Retains all original nutrients and beneficial compounds\n- Typically unfiltered\n- Often sold directly by local beekeepers\n\nPure Honey:\n- Processed to remove impurities\n- Heated and filtered\n- Smoother, more uniform appearance\n- May have added ingredients or corn syrup\n- Some nutrients and enzymes can be lost during processing\n- Longer shelf life\n- Typically found in commercial stores\n\nBoth can be 100% honey, but raw honey is considered more natural and nutritionally dense.",
